parameters.name: AudioJson
parameters.description: Output audio voice and format; only applicable to the Qwen-Omni model, provided that the modalities parameter is set to \["text", "audio"].

parameters.name: DesensitizationRule
parameters.description: Masking category. Required when needDataMasking is true.

parameters.name: Dimensions
parameters.description: The embedding dimensions.

parameters.name: EnableCodeInterpreter
parameters.description: Specifies whether to enable the code interpreter feature. Takes effect only when model is qwen3-max-preview and enable_thinking is true.

parameters.name: EnableSearch
parameters.description: Whether to enable web search.

parameters.name: EnableThinking
parameters.description: Specifies whether to enable thinking mode when using hybrid thinking models.

parameters.name: IncludeUsage
parameters.description: Specifies whether to include token usage information in the final chunk of the streaming response.

parameters.name: Input
parameters.description: The input to the embedding model.

parameters.name: InstanceId
parameters.description: The ID of the instance, used to specify the corresponding data masking rules. You can call the [ListInstances](~~141936~~) or [GetInstance](~~141567~~) operation to query the ID of the instance.

parameters.name: Logprobs
parameters.description: Specifies whether to return the log probabilities of the output tokens.

parameters.name: MaxTokens
parameters.description: Limits the maximum number of tokens the model can generate. If the output exceeds this value, generation will be truncated. Suitable for scenarios where you need to control the output length.

parameters.name: Messages
parameters.description: The conversation context passed to the model, arranged in chronological order.

parameters.name: ModalitiesList
parameters.description: Output data modality; only applicable to the Qwen-Omni model.

parameters.name: Model
parameters.description: The model name. Supported models: Qwen series text-only Large Language Models (commercial and open-source). Multi-modal models are not supported.

parameters.name: NeedDesensitization
parameters.description: Whether to enable data masking. Defaults to false.

parameters.name: Parameters
parameters.description: Model configuration parameters.

parameters.name: PresencePenalty
parameters.description: Controls the degree of repetition in generated text. Valid values: \[-2.0, 2.0]. Positive values decrease repetition, while negative values increase it.

parameters.name: ResponseFormat
parameters.description: The format of the returned content. Valid values: text: Plain text response; json_object: Standardized JSON string.

parameters.name: SearchOptions
parameters.description: Web search strategy.

parameters.name: Seed
parameters.description: Random seed. Used to ensure the reproducibility of results under the same input and parameters. Valid values: \[0, 2^31âˆ’1].

parameters.name: Stop
parameters.description: Stop sequences.

parameters.name: Stream
parameters.description: Specifies whether to use streaming output.

parameters.name: Temperature
parameters.description: The sampling temperature controls the diversity of the generated text. The higher the temperature, the more diverse the generated text, and conversely, the more deterministic the generated text. Valid values: \[0, 2).

parameters.name: ThinkingBudget
parameters.description: The maximum number of tokens allowed for the model's internal reasoning process.

parameters.name: TopK
parameters.description: Specifies the number of candidate tokens to consider during sampling. Higher values increase randomness, while lower values make the output more deterministic. Set to null or a value greater than 100 to disable.

parameters.name: TopLogprobs
parameters.description: Specifies the number of most likely candidate tokens to return at each generation step. Valid values: \[0, 5].

parameters.name: TopP
parameters.description: The probability threshold for nucleus sampling, used to control the diversity of the generated text. Higher Top-P values result in more diverse generated text. Valid values: (0,1.0].

parameters.name: VlHighResolutionImages
parameters.description: Specifies whether to increase the maximum pixel limit of input images to the equivalent of 16,384 tokens.

parameters.name: XDashScopeDataInspection
parameters.description: Specifies whether to further identify non-compliant information in both input and output content, building upon the built-in content safety capabilities of the Tongyi Qianwen API.
